But I have to admit that about half a year ago, you might have perhaps thought of me in the same way :/  I played EQ for a couple years, then quit for like 2.5 years and just came back around 6 months ago.  When I came back, I had NO idea what was going on with TONS of things, not only eq in general, but even my much beloved bard class.  And one of the many many things that were new to me was that they were bard songs that were AE, not group only.  I was floored! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
There were always a million abreviations to remember, now there's about a billion.  There were always tons of spells to remember for all the classes, now there's 10 times more and a zillion new alternate abilities and disciplines to boot.  It used to be hard enough to remember everything you could about the 50 zones in the game, now theres 150 to learn about and try to retain.  I swear it's comparable to working full time and going to school full time simultaneously  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-3.gif" border="0" alt="Scared" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

