				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: If you are ebayed...<a name="36391"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 25 04 5:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just yesterday, I was grouped with two people who were boxing.  The first had a cleric, rogue, and shadow knight.  The other was a chanter and a mage.  Now I didn't know this at first, and I was getting a little edgy when the group was so quiet.  The thing that set off the most alarm bells was when the cleric/SK/rogue asked &quot;so what do bards do, anyway?  I'm kinda new.&quot;  Normally I would be happy to oblige his question, but this is an all-65 group going into an LDoN.  Not hard, but still...  So I explain the basics of our abilities, no big deal.  Then when I asked &quot;want me to pull?&quot; he says &quot;how do you pull?&quot;  I quickly answered &quot;one at a time, of course.&quot;  I was starting to get a little nervous/peeved when he said something along the lines of &quot;ok well, you just break the room and I'll pull.&quot;  Naturally I didn't want anyone moving in on my game, 'specially someone who's 3 boxing the tank and the main healer, so I just pulled fast enough so they had no time to argue.  What got me angry was when he looted a 6agi aug without saying a word.  Wouldn't bother me if it was a sv anything but magic or something like that, but I need better agi :\ So I see it whizz by on my window, and proceed with the usual &quot;wtf, man?&quot;  &quot;you're going too fast, I didn't know it was an aug, sorry.&quot;  BS, unless your gems look different cause your UI is screwed and you have confirmation turned off for no drop (the latter seems like a bad idea to me in the first place).  So I just keep pulling at a pace where I don't have to talk the rest of the time, get us a win, and make tracks over to HoH to catch a trial.  The moral is, well I dunno... I just found it kind of unnerving to be playing with 2 multiboxers with all level 65 characters who don't even know anything about what bards do.  Might have been a little E-bayed.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
